subSection.paragraph:
Prokaryotic and eukaryotic microorganisms establish an intestinal microbiome in mammals (
Bernardes et al., 2020
; 
Parfrey et al., 2011
). Metabolites and metabolic signals of intestinal microorganisms are beneficial for defining the trajectory toward host health or disease, especially early in life (
Arrieta et al., 2014
; 
Honda and Littman, 2016
; 
Laforest-Lapointe and Arrieta, 2017
). Some studies have demonstrated that changes in the microbiome are associated with host physiological disorders and increased susceptibility to inflammation and metabolic and neurogenic diseases (
Cryan et al., 2019
; 
Lynch and Pedersen, 2016
). For example, 

Saccharomyces boulardii

is a yeast probiotic that is able to prevent and treat pathogenic bacterial infections and intestinal complications (
Hatoum et al., 2012
). To date, studies on gut microbiota have mainly focused on bacteria; however, intestinal fungi are an integral part of a wide variety of human gut microbial environments, and their functional ecological role in human gut microbiomes is still unclear (
Bernardes et al., 2020
). Therefore, enhancing the study of metabolites of intestinal fungi is very important to elucidate the underlying relationship between gut fungi and the host (
Bernardes et al., 2020
; 
Nash et al., 2017
).

The genus 

Penicillium

is a cosmopolite ascomycetous fungus widely distributed in marine and terrestrial environments, as well as in the human gut. This genus comprises more than 300 species, and some species are capable of elaborating metabolites with peculiar structural features and significant biological activities, including alkaloids (e.g., penazaphilones A–I) (
Tang et al., 2019
), sesquiterpene coumarins (e.g., penisarins A and B) (
Li et al., 2020
), cyclic peptides (psychrophilins B and C) (
Dalsgaard et al., 2004
), and polyketides (e.g., minolutelides A and B, sclerotiorin, and citrofulvicin) (
Chidananda and Sattur, 2007
; 
Iida et al., 2008
). Some metabolites display anti-inflammatory, antiproliferative, and anti-osteoporotic activities, as well as the inhibition of lipoxygenase-1 (
Chen et al., 2018
; 
Chidananda and Sattur, 2007
; 
Iida et al., 2008
), which has attracted attention from pharmacists and chemists.

